<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The example here doesn't work <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.mail.multiple-emails.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>Zend_Mail_Transport_Smtp does not even have connect() or disconnect() methods!</p>

<p>The transport itself automatically creates a connection when sending the first email -- it provides no mechanism for doing so beforehand.</p>

<p>Perhaps the example should include something like the following:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$conn = new Zend_Mail_Protocol_Smtp($host, $port);
$conn-&gt;connect();

$tr = new Zend_Mail_Transport_Smtp;
$tr-&gt;setConnection($conn);
</code></pre>

